title: For Sale:  Winchester 1873 44-40 W/set trigger & letter 1876
postcontent:
Winchester model 1873 chambered for 44-40. This is an early 1st model built in 1876. The features consistent with an early 1st model are the script style serial number (256XX), a flush fit screw in magazine plug, the proper roll stamp on the barrel, the lack of a trigger block button, the early style lever lock, and the early tang marking. The dust cover is the 4th version of the early style. The hammer looks to me like the second variation but it is hard to tell from the photo's that I have to compare it with. It is equipped with a special order 30 inch barrel and a set trigger. The bluing on the barrel and magazine tube rates about 75% or better. It shows some edge and muzzle wear and has a few small dings on the top corners. The receiver has some old pitting in areas and my have had some finish applied. There are no serious flaws in the wood just a few light handling marks. The bore on a scale of 1 to 10 rates about an 8. It is reasonably bright with strong rifling but has a just little crud in a couple of the groves. It is far better than most of the 73 barrels you see out there ..

I will ship to your location ..

Buyers, however, may take any number of extras we have on hand at the same per-holster price, and with no additional shipping charges. Southpaws, don’t despair! At press time we had Left Hand versions for $10 apiece less. If you can’t find the Left Hand ad, just give us a shout. Next to the company's pioneering work with Kevlar Body Armor in the 1970s, the SSII Security Duty Holster is Safariland's chief contribution to the safety of our Peace Officers. The SSII, of course, is their most popular, high level security duty holster. This Mid-Ride Level II Retention Holster guards against anyone grabbing an officer’s sidearm during an emergency or altercation. This holster is relatively simple to operate, but we recommend studying the instruction manual. This is a standard Jacket Slot SSII to fit Glock Models 17, 22, and 31 that are equipped with Glock GTL series tactical lights, including the GTL10, GTL21/22, and GTL51/52 lights. Manufacturer is Safariland / BAE Systems of Ontario, CA. Construction is Kevlar reinforced Safari-Laminate with double set screws for the Sam Browne Duty Rig with up to 3 inch wide belts. Interior is suede lined to guard against wear to the sidearm. The key to this system and to the holster is the spring loaded thumb releasing top strap retention that enables a trained operator to depress the thumb tab and move the strap forward rapidly, and clear leather quickly. Safariland Model Number is 6280-837-81. For owners of Glock models 17, 22, or 31; and for that matter, models 19, 23, and 32, we have inserted a measured piece of 1 inch PVC that is for Glock owners who do not have a factory light with their pistol. The PVC will easily remove with a pair of pliers. Since only the slide and lower grip frame dimensions are different on models 19 and 23, it will work correctly with either of those pistols. Since a Glock 17 or 22 has a frame thickness of 1.15 inches, and a slide thickness of 1.08; and an overall slide length of 7 3/8 inches from the back of the slide to the barrel muzzle, this holster will certainly accommodate other pistols with those dimensions. Glock 20 and 21 series pistols will NOT work, they’re too thick. Since the kicker is usually the trigger guard on holster interchangeability, a person with, say, an SW99 can alter or replace the PVC piece. We inserted, for instance, a Walther / Smith & Wesson SW99 .40 caliber; an SD9; a standard Glock 17; and a Smith & Wesson MP40 and they all fit well enough. Replacement price on this fine holster is upwards of $150.00. The holsters in the photos are all new and unissued in their factory packaging, and these came to us as surplus from a police trade in Smith & Wesson’s home town. Next to the company's pioneering work with Kevlar Body Armor in the 1970s, the SSII Security Duty Holster is Safariland's chief contribution to the safety of our Peace Officers. The SSII, of course, is their most popular, high level security duty holster. This Mid-Ride Level II Retention Holster guards against anyone grabbing an officer’s sidearm during an emergency or altercation. This holster is relatively simple to operate, but we recommend studying the instruction manual. This is a standard Jacket Slot SSII to fit Glock Models 17 and 22 that are equipped with Glock GTL series tactical lights, including the GTL10, GTL21/22, and GTL51/52 lights. Construction is Kevlar reinforced Safari-Laminate with double set screws for the Sam Browne Duty Rig with up to 3 inch wide belts. Interior is suede lined to guard against wear to the sidearm. The key to this system and to the holster is the spring loaded thumb releasing top strap retention that enables a trained operator to depress the thumb tab and move the strap forward rapidly, and clear leather quickly. Safariland Model Number is 6280-837-82. For Southpaw owners of Glock models 17 and 22; and for that matter, models 19 and 23, we have inserted a measured piece of 1 inch PVC that is for Glock totin’ Southpaws who do not have a factory light with their pistol. The PVC will easily remove with a pair of pliers. Since only the slide and lower grip frame dimensions are different on models 19 and 23, it will work correctly with either of those pistols. Since a Glock 17 or 22 has a frame thickness of 1.15 inches, and a slide thickness of 1.08; and an overall slide length of 7 3/8 inches from the back of the slide to the barrel muzzle, this holster will certainly accommodate other pistols with those dimensions. Since the kicker is usually the trigger guard on holster interchangeability, a person with, say, an SW99 can alter or replace the PVC piece. We inserted, for instance, a Walther / Smith & Wesson SW99 .40 caliber; an SD9; a standard Glock 17; and a Smith & Wesson MP40 and they all fit well enough. Additional inner tanks can be purchased separately. Hanging cords have been integrated into the design to allow large objects to take full advantage of the ultrasonic energy. Additionally, the Hot Tub® features integrated drain pans in the lids, a small parts basket, a degas function and 5 temperature settings from 100-140°F.
